2025-09-02  Hayaki Saito <saitoha@me.com>

	* src/quant.c: dither: split error_diffuse() into three strategies
	and improve perceptual quality 1. error_diffuse_fast(): integer math 2. error_diffuse_normal(): integer math with truncation-error
	compensation 3. error_diffuse_precise(): compute diffusion weights in double and
	cast on accumulation usage: - use precise for algorithms with large denominators (~48), e.g.,
	jajuni, stucki - use normal for medium denominators (~16), e.g., floyd-steinberg,
	burkes - use fast for atkinson and lso1 this change reduces banding and speckling and yields visibly cleaner
	results, with the biggest gains on jajuni and stucki

2025-09-01  Hayaki Saito <saitoha@me.com>

